# Responsive layouts (no half-ass breakpoints)

UI must be **designed per breakpoint**, not a phone stack stretched until it looks sparse. If a wide viewport could belong to an unfinished mock, the layout failed.

Home and tools must feel like the **same product width** when navigating — do not let `/` be a stray wider canvas than guides/tools.

## Page shell scale (required)

Use [`PageShell`](src/components/layout/PageShell.tsx) / [`PAGE_SHELL`](src/lib/constants/page-shell.ts) — do not invent one-off `max-w-*` for page frames.

| Tier | Class | Use |
|------|--------|-----|
| `chrome` | `max-w-7xl` | Header, footer, hub nav/banner only |
| `wide` | `max-w-5xl` | Home, examples, multi-panel tools (default) |
| `read` | `max-w-3xl` | Guides, privacy, long-form |
| `focus` | `max-w-2xl` | Brand kit, manifesto, forms |

Within a shell, still constrain body copy (`max-w-prose` / `max-w-xl`) when needed. Adapt grids at `sm`/`md`/`lg` so `wide` does not become four cramped columns — prefer intentional density (e.g. home channels: 2×2, not 4 skinny cols).

## Hard rejects (fix before shipping)

- **Stray wide home** — marketing/home at `max-w-7xl` while tools/guides sit at `5xl`/`3xl`
- **Stretched mobile shell** — same single column, left-pinned blocks, growing empty space as the viewport widens
- **Orphan empty containers** — full-width cards whose content is a short left-aligned list with a dead zone filling the rest
- **Unbounded measure** — body copy running >~65–75ch without a readable constraint
- **Breakpoint blindness** — only `px-4` + `max-w-*` and no intentional change at `sm` / `md` / `lg`
- **CTA row as afterthought** — buttons left-dumped with no wrap/stack plan across widths

## Do this instead

1. **Pick a shell tier first**, then compose for desktop / stack for mobile
2. **Fill or constrain** — use the width (grid/columns/rail) or shrink the surface; never a wide empty card
3. **Chrome vs body** — chrome may be `7xl`; page body uses `wide`/`read`/`focus`. Edges share `px-4`; do not mix random max-widths for the same page type
4. **Verify three widths** — ~375, ~768, ~1280: each must look intentional

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — home wider than every other public page
<div className="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4">…

// ✅ GOOD
<PageShell className="py-8 md:py-12">…
<PageShell size="read" className="py-12">… // guides
```

## Checklist (any new/changed page or major layout)

- [ ] Shell tier matches page type (`wide` / `read` / `focus`)
- [ ] Desktop is not just mobile with more margin
- [ ] No full-bleed empty regions inside bordered/filled surfaces
- [ ] Body measure stays readable
- [ ] Spot-checked phone / tablet / desktop
